This documentation describes the Aerospike Service Broker for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF). The Aerospike Service Broker registers a service broker on PCF and exposes its service plans on the Marketplace. Developers can provision application services on an existing Aerospike database by creating instances of the service plans using Apps Manager or the cf Command Line Interface (CLI).

## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

Aerospike is a high performance, distributed, scalable NoSQL database and key/value store. The Aerospike Service Broker for PCF is designed to be used with an already deployed Aerospike database and will automatically discover the [namespaces](http://www.aerospike.com/docs/architecture/data-model.html) which have been created on the database and expose them as service plans which can be used to create services within PCF. These services can then be bound to applications deployed in PCF providing connection information to the applications.

For more information, see the [Aerospike documentation](http://www.aerospike.com/docs/)

