## <a id="reqs"></a>Requirements

To use the Aerospike Service Broker, you must have an Aerospike database server already deployed. The database should have a namespace configured which will be used by the Aerospike Service Broker to store service and application binding information. If using the Enterprise Edition of the server, there should also be a user configured with read-write permissions to the designated namespace as well as user-admin permissions since the Service Broker will create/delete users during the application binding/unbinding operations.

